content.body:
### Shop 285/75R16 Tire Size
285/75R16 is an older tire size that was found on 2000s Hummers. If you drive a 2006-2010 era Hummer H3 or H3T then there’s a good chance you have 285/75R16 tires, and a brand new version of either of these vehicles might’ve rolled out of the factory with a set of [Bridgestone Dueler A/T RH-S](https://simpletire.com/brands/bridgestone-tires/dueler-a-t-rh-s) tires attached.

Popular Vehicles
2006-2010 Hummer H3
2009-2010 Hummer H3T

Most drivers only all-season tires thanks to their ability to perform well in dry, wet, and light winter weather conditions. Check out the Michelin Defender LTX M/S, [Yokohama Geolandar H/T G056](https://simpletire.com/brands/yokohama-tires/geolandar-h-t-g056), and Falken Wildpeak H/T02, if you need a set of 285/75R16 tires that provide year-round traction and performance.

Some drivers like to take their Hummer H3 or H3T off-road from time to time, so they need a set of tires that can perform on any terrain. All-terrain tires are designed for on- and off-road traction, so take a look at the Continental TerrainContact A/T, BFGoodrich All-Terrain T/A KO2, or [GT Radial Adventuro AT3](https://simpletire.com/brands/gt-radial-tires/adventuro-at3) if you want great performance on any terrain.

Drivers who spend a lot of time off-road might need a tire that’s a bit stronger and offers better traction in mud, dirt, and rocks than an all-terrain tire. Mud terrain tires are built for the drivers who want to conquer any terrain, and tires like the [Nitto Trail Grappler M/T](https://simpletire.com/brands/nitto-tires/trail-grappler-m-t), Kumho Road Venture MT71, and Nexen Roadian MTX are a great option to get you through deep mud and tough rocks.

Whether you drive a Hummer H3, Hummer H3T or something else, SimpleTire has a set of 285/75R16 tires that meets your needs at a great price!
